        <hr noshade size="2" color="#545A7D">
        
         I thought they fixed that Sword of Runes proc with pets so that it only works on summoned things now (like it's supposed to).  Other mage summonings can sure be nice, though.</P><P>Dual wielding starts with the occasional rare 24 pet.  The 39 pet is the first pet that reliably dual wields without being given weapons.  (There was some Verantish reason for that, I forget now what it was.)</P><P>The pets will take their damage rating from the weapon, if the weapon's damage is higher than their own.  That's really handy at level 1 and becomes irrelevant around level 16.  Level 4 pets with halberds are pretty impressive at level 4.</P><P>Giving a single weapon to your pet will get him to walk less like a doofus and more like a minion of evil.  Might only be true if you have the Luclin human model enabled, though.</P><P>I'm a fan of the Gnoll Hide Lariat myself, but I'm usually too lazy to go to South Karana and get them.  Stun procs are nice.</P><P><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=247832" target="_blank">Morty Undercrypt</a>, Keeper of the <a href="http://www.necrognomicon.com/" target="_blank">NecroGnomicon</a><BR><font size=1>"I am the truth, and the truth shall make you flee."</font id=size1><BR>E'ci<a href="#top"><img src="icon_go_up.gif" height="15" width="15" border="0" align="right" alt="Go to Top of Page"></a></font></td>
