        &nbsp;<a href="post.asp?method=ReplyQuote&amp;REPLY_ID=42633&amp;TOPIC_ID=5197&amp;FORUM_ID=3&amp;CAT_ID=1&amp;Forum_Title=Necromancer+Game+Guides&amp;Topic_Title=Giving+weapons+to+pets&amp;M="><img src="icon_reply_topic.gif" height="15" width="15" alt="Reply with Quote" border="0" align="absmiddle" hspace="6"></a>

        <hr noshade size="2" color="#545A7D">
        
         The Swords of Runes were changed ages ago to only proc against only summoned monsters.  That said, if you can get into a zone with summoned monsters (Hole is a good one, bees in BW are also summoned for some reason) they will proc a lot.   Your best bet if you want cheap, easy proccing weapons is to, assuming you are 40 something of course, go smack some Tizmaks, they seem to drop a lot of Velium weapons.</P><P>Lately I've taken to looting the occasional rusty just to give a few weapons to ol' boney.   Can't stand that walk.  For the most part though, few weapons will give your pet an edge, not counting procs, past the aforementioned 16th.  At one point, the Weighted Axe could be used by pets, resulting in some rather intense damage, but that has long since been changed.  However, there is no reduction in how fast your pet hits, no matter what weapon you give it.  That was changed a very long time ago.  The only reduction you will see if from haste spells/effects on your pet.</P><P><i><b><font color=gold><font size=4>Dinomight Questaholic</b></font id=size4><BR>Master of the Lizard Dance on Test  {The Grove}</i></font id=gold></P><P>Edited by - Dinomight on 06/21/2002  14:45:42<a href="#top"><img src="icon_go_up.gif" height="15" width="15" border="0" align="right" alt="Go to Top of Page"></a></font></td>
